# RECITALS

CIOG is responsible for ensuring that the Department of Defence has a dependable, secure and integrated ICT environment to support the Department of Defence's business and military operations. CIOG's infrastructure is integral to core Department of Defence's functions, including intelligence, surveillance, reconnaissance, communications, information warfare, logistics, command and management. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}  

From time to time the Commonwealth may require the provision of certain ICT services to support CIOG's functions and activities and those of the Commonwealth more broadly. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}  

The Commonwealth has established this standing offer ICT Provider Arrangement with a number of suppliers to provide certain ICT services. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}  

The Supplier has agreed to provide the Services on the terms set out in this Deed and any Work Order formed under this Deed. :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}  

